{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|&gt;ᶜ_»\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_|&gt;ᶜ_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The `CreateAnnihilate` value of a `CrAnFieldOp`s, i.e. whether it is a creation or\nannihilation operator. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|>ᶜ_»","kind":"def","line":136,"name":"FieldSpecification.«term_|>ᶜ_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L136-L139"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|&gt;ₛ__3»\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_|&gt;ₛ__3»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, and an element `φ` in `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, the field\nstatistic `crAnStatistics φ` is defined to be the statistic associated with the field `𝓕.Field`\n(or the `𝓕.FieldOp`) underlying `φ`.\n\nThe following notation is used in relation to `crAnStatistics`:\n- For `φ` an element of `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φ` is `crAnStatistics φ`.\n- For `φs` a list of `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φs` is the product of `crAnStatistics φ` over\n  the list `φs`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|>ₛ__3»","kind":"def","line":132,"name":"FieldSpecification.«term_|>ₛ__3»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L132-L134"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|&gt;ₛ__2»\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_|&gt;ₛ__2»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, and an element `φ` in `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, the field\nstatistic `crAnStatistics φ` is defined to be the statistic associated with the field `𝓕.Field`\n(or the `𝓕.FieldOp`) underlying `φ`.\n\nThe following notation is used in relation to `crAnStatistics`:\n- For `φ` an element of `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φ` is `crAnStatistics φ`.\n- For `φs` a list of `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φs` is the product of `crAnStatistics φ` over\n  the list `φs`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|>ₛ__2»","kind":"def","line":128,"name":"FieldSpecification.«term_|>ₛ__2»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L128-L130"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.crAnStatistics\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">crAnStatistics</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.CrAnFieldOp\">CrAnFieldOp</a></span> → <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldStatistics/Basic.html#FieldStatistic\">FieldStatistic</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, and an element `φ` in `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, the field\nstatistic `crAnStatistics φ` is defined to be the statistic associated with the field `𝓕.Field`\n(or the `𝓕.FieldOp`) underlying `φ`.\n\nThe following notation is used in relation to `crAnStatistics`:\n- For `φ` an element of `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φ` is `crAnStatistics φ`.\n- For `φs` a list of `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φs` is the product of `crAnStatistics φ` over\n  the list `φs`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.crAnStatistics","kind":"def","line":116,"name":"FieldSpecification.crAnStatistics","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L116-L126"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.crAnFieldOpToCreateAnnihilate\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">crAnFieldOpToCreateAnnihilate</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.CrAnFieldOp\">CrAnFieldOp</a></span> → <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/CreateAnnihilate.html#CreateAnnihilate\">CreateAnnihilate</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, `𝓕.crAnFieldOpToCreateAnnihilate` is the map from\n  `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp` to `CreateAnnihilate` taking `φ` to `create` if\n- `φ` corresponds to an incoming asymptotic field operator or the creation part of a position based\n  field operator.\n\notherwise it takes `φ` to `annihilate`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.crAnFieldOpToCreateAnnihilate","kind":"def","line":103,"name":"FieldSpecification.crAnFieldOpToCreateAnnihilate","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L103-L114"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.crAnFieldOpToFieldOp_prod\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">crAnFieldOpToFieldOp_prod</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCrAnType\">fieldOpToCrAnType</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.crAnFieldOpToFieldOp\">crAnFieldOpToFieldOp</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Sigma.mk\">⟨</a><span class=\"fn\">s</span>, <span class=\"fn\">t</span><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Sigma.mk\">⟩</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.crAnFieldOpToFieldOp_prod","kind":"theorem","line":99,"name":"FieldSpecification.crAnFieldOpToFieldOp_prod","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L99-L101"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.crAnFieldOpToFieldOp\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">crAnFieldOpToFieldOp</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.CrAnFieldOp\">CrAnFieldOp</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The map from creation and annihilation field operator to their underlying states. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.crAnFieldOpToFieldOp","kind":"def","line":96,"name":"FieldSpecification.crAnFieldOpToFieldOp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L96-L97"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.CrAnFieldOp\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">CrAnFieldOp</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, the (sigma) type `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`\ncorresponds to the type of creation and annihilation parts of field operators.\nIt formally defined to consist of the following elements:\n- For each incoming asymptotic field operator `φ` in `𝓕.FieldOp` an element\n  written as `⟨φ, ()⟩` in `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, corresponding to the creation part of `φ`.\n  Here `φ` has no annihilation part. (Here `()` is the unique element of `Unit`.)\n- For each position field operator `φ` in `𝓕.FieldOp` an element of `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`\n  written as `⟨φ, .create⟩`, corresponding to the creation part of `φ`.\n- For each position field operator `φ` in `𝓕.FieldOp` an element of `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`\n  written as `⟨φ, .annihilate⟩`, corresponding to the annihilation part of `φ`.\n- For each outgoing asymptotic field operator `φ` in `𝓕.FieldOp` an element\n  written as `⟨φ, ()⟩` in `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`, corresponding to the annihilation part of `φ`.\n  Here `φ` has no creation part. (Here `()` is the unique element of `Unit`.)\n\nAs an example, if `f` corresponds to a Weyl-fermion field, it would contribute\n  the following elements to `𝓕.CrAnFieldOp`\n- For each spin `s`, an element corresponding to an incoming asymptotic operator: `a(p, s)`.\n- For each each Lorentz\n  index `a`, an element corresponding to the creation part of a position operator:\n\n  `∑ s, ∫ d³p/(…) (xₐ (p,s) a(p, s) e ^ (-i p x))`.\n- For each each Lorentz\n  index `a`,an element corresponding to annihilation part of a position operator:\n\n  `∑ s, ∫ d³p/(…) (yₐ(p,s) a†(p, s) e ^ (-i p x))`.\n- For each spin `s`, element corresponding to an outgoing asymptotic operator: `a†(p, s)`.\n\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.CrAnFieldOp","kind":"def","line":65,"name":"FieldSpecification.CrAnFieldOp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L65-L94"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCreateAnnihilateTypeCongr\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">fieldOpToCreateAnnihilateTypeCongr</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">i </span><span class=\"fn\">j</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">i</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">j</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCrAnType\">fieldOpToCrAnType</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Equiv/Defs.html#Equiv\">≃</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCrAnType\">fieldOpToCrAnType</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">j</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The equivalence between `𝓕.fieldOpToCreateAnnihilateType i` and\n`𝓕.fieldOpToCreateAnnihilateType j` from an equality `i = j`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCreateAnnihilateTypeCongr","kind":"def","line":59,"name":"FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCreateAnnihilateTypeCongr","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L59-L63"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.instDecidableEqFieldOpToCrAnType\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">instDecidableEqFieldOpToCrAnType</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#DecidableEq\">DecidableEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCrAnType\">fieldOpToCrAnType</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The instance of a decidable equality on `𝓕.fieldOpToCreateAnnihilateType i`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.instDecidableEqFieldOpToCrAnType","kind":"instance","line":52,"name":"FieldSpecification.instDecidableEqFieldOpToCrAnType","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L52-L57"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.instFintypeFieldOpToCrAnType\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">instFintypeFieldOpToCrAnType</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Fintype/Defs.html#Fintype\">Fintype</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCrAnType\">fieldOpToCrAnType</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The instance of a finite type on `𝓕.fieldOpToCreateAnnihilateType i`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.instFintypeFieldOpToCrAnType","kind":"instance","line":45,"name":"FieldSpecification.instFintypeFieldOpToCrAnType","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L45-L50"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCrAnType\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">fieldOpToCrAnType</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"To each field operator the specification of the type of creation and annihilation parts.\nFor asymptotic states there is only one allowed part, whilst for position\nfield operator there is two. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/CrAnFieldOp.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCrAnType","kind":"def","line":37,"name":"FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCrAnType","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L37-L43"}}],"imports":["Init","PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.FieldSpecification.Basic","PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.CreateAnnihilate"],"instances":[{"className":"Fintype","name":"FieldSpecification.instFintypeFieldOpToCrAnType","typeNames":["FieldSpecification.fieldOpToCrAnType"]},{"className":"Decidable","name":"FieldSpecification.instDecidableEqFieldOpToCrAnType","typeNames":["Eq"]}],"name":"PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.FieldSpecification.CrAnFieldOp"}